metadata.name: Smaug - The guardian of the old mining town
metadata.description:
El Triunfo took on special relevance in the 19th century, where the gold and silver mines made it the most populated community in Baja California Sur at that time. Today still keeps in its corners vestiges of the architecture and the greatness of this town.

If you want to learn more about this very interesting town click the link below.

https://www.museorutadeplata.com

https://www.mexicodesconocido.com.mx/el-triunfo-del-auge-al-abandono-baja-california.html

Location: El Triunfo, La Paz; Baja California Sur. Mexico.
